    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWindows did not support underline syles other than the regular one. no undercurl or double line . but with the latest merge one month ago these has been implemented and planned for  https://github.com/microsoft/terminal/pull/16097.\r\n\r\nin the latest canary you can see this in action using powershell >= 6  (Cmd as far as i know does not support escape chars. correct me if i am wrong )\r\n\r\nusing both \r\n```\r\nWrite-Host \"`e[4:3mtest`e[0m\"\r\nWrite-Host \"`e[4:3;58:2::000:255:000mtest`e[0m\"\r\n```\r\nwill print both colored non colored undercurl \r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/27051374/1c559811-e124-4354-8d67-cacc0f3f78a2)\r\n\r\nbut neovim in windows won't show these even when modifying the t_Ce and t_Cs variables\r\n\r\n```\r\nif vim.fn.has(\"termguicolors\") == 1 then\r\n    vim.o.termguicolors = true\r\n    -- Enable undercurl\r\n    vim.api.nvim_set_var('t_Cs', '\\\\e[4:3m')\r\n    vim.api.nvim_set_var('t_Ce', '\\\\e[4:0m')\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nCan this be implemented early so when the final release is done this wil be ready?\r\nthe latest canary also supports all other styles of underline like dotted and double underlines.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nto show undercurls and other styles of  underlines",
